<tal:value condition="nocall:context/biography">
<dl class="personBiography"
    tal:define="output python:context.biography.output_relative_to(view.context)"
    tal:condition="output">
    <dt i18n:domain="collective.roster" i18n:translate="">Biography</dt>
    <dd tal:content="structure output" />
</dl>
</tal:value>
<tal:comment replace="nothing">
Rendering RichText is not as trivial as it looks. We must render it using its
output_relative_to-method to get relative links (e.g. anchors) rendered
correctly.

https://raw.github.com/plone/plone.app.textfield/master/plone/app/textfield/widget_display.pt

To avoid this, we could use plone.directives.dexterity.DisplayForm and
display widgets instead of manually rendering field's content.
</tal:comment>
